Ta hanyar binciken microscope na lantarki, an gano ƙwayoyin SARS-CoV-2 a cikin ƙananan ƙananan epithelium na hanyar numfashi na mutum.
ACE2 na mutum an san shi da mai karɓar kwayar cutar SARS-CoV-2 da kuma SARS-CoV.
Koyaya, furotin S na SARS-CoV-2 yana da rauni a haɗuwa da mai karɓar ACE2 na ɗan adam fiye da SARS-CoV, wanda ya dace da gaskiyar cewa SARS-CoV-2 yana haifar da rashin lafiya fiye da SARS-CoV.
SARS-CoV-2 kuma yana samar da sabon ɗan gajeren furotin wanda aka tsara ta hanyar orf3b da furotin mai ɓoyewa wanda aka tsara ta hanyar orf8.
Furotin orf3b na SARS-CoV-2 yana da tasiri a cikin yanayin cutar ta cutar kuma yana hana bayyanar IFNβ (interferon beta); duk da haka, orf8 ba ya ƙunshe da wani abu na biyu ko dalili na aiki.
A ranar 18 ga Fabrairu, 2020, Zhou da abokan aikinsa sun ba da rahoton tsarin microscopy na lantarki na mutum na ACE2 mai karɓar ƙarfin hali na 2.9 ingstrom a cikin hadaddun tare da mai ɗaukar amino acid mai suna B0AT1.
Sun gano cewa hadaddun da ke sama, wanda ke da buɗewa da rufewa, ana haɗa shi a cikin dimer kuma hadaddun ACE2-B0AT1 na iya haɗawa da sunadarai biyu na S waɗanda za a iya amfani da su azaman ma'auni don ganowa da kamuwa da cutar coronavirus.
B0AT1 na iya zama maƙasudin magani don tantance magunguna don magance kamuwa da cutar SARS-CoV-2.
